1. Setup Using Maven (pom.xml)
If you are using Maven for your project, you can add the JUnit Jupiter dependency to your pom.xml file.

<dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>
        <artifactId>junit-jupiter</artifactId>
        <version>5.10.2</version>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>

After adding the dependency, you can run your tests using mvn test from your terminal, or by right-clicking the test class in your IDE and choosing Run As > JUnit Test.

2. Setup in Eclipse (No Maven)
For projects in Eclipse without Maven, follow these steps to add the JUnit library:

Right-click on your project in the Project Explorer.

Select Build Path > Configure Build Path....

Go to the Libraries tab.

Click the Add Library... button.

Choose JUnit from the list of libraries.

Select JUnit 5 as the JUnit version.

Click Finish.

Finally, click Apply and Close to save the changes.